132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 835
S.P. 368 In Senate, March 4, 2025
An Act to Allow Children to Participate in Beano Games Conducted
by Nonprofit Charitable Organizations
Reference to the Committee on Veterans and Legal Affairs suggested and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator BERNARD of Aroostook.
Cosponsored by Senator: TIMBERLAKE of Androscoggin.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 17 MRSA §313-D, sub-§5 is enacted to read:
3 5. Nonprofit charitable organizations; no fee. A bona fide nonprofit charitable,
4 educational, political, civic, recreational, fraternal, patriotic, religious or veterans'
5 organization when:
6 A. Games are offered exclusively to a club, group or organization composed of
7 individuals at least 90% of whom are under 18 years of age or to an incorporated
8 community organization, agency or institution;
9 B. Games are offered exclusively on the premises of the bona fide nonprofit charitable,
10 educational, political, civic, recreational, fraternal, patriotic, religious or veterans'
11 organization conducting beano; and
12 C. No fee is charged to participate in a beano game.
13 Sec. 2. 17 MRSA §313-D, 2nd ¶, as enacted by PL 2017, c. 284, Pt. JJJJJ, §7, is
14 amended to read:
15 Notwithstanding section 319, persons under the age of 16 years of age may take part
16 in a game of beano conducted under subsection 2, 3 or, 4 or 5.
17 SUMMARY
1188 This bill authorizes bona fide nonprofit charitable, educational, political, civic,
1199 recreational, fraternal, patriotic, religious or veterans' organizations to conduct beano
2200 without a license or without registering with the Department of Public Safety, Gambling
2211 Control Unit when beano games are offered exclusively to a club, group or organization
2222 composed of individuals at least 90% of whom are under 18 years of age or to an
2233 incorporated community organization, agency or institution, games are offered exclusively
2244 on the premises of the organization conducting beano and there is no fee charged to
2255 participate in a beano game.
